Virtos Dextrum's office. It's the office he works in. It's the location he filmed the video played at one point in The Antarctica Project. It is connected to a room central to another Project by that name which is related but distinct.

Virtos Dextrum would often sleep here rather than going home. In earlier days of his career it was a necessity, since he still hadn't moved fully to the capital, but sometimes it became a matter of convenience. He blurred the line between studiousness and sloth. Did he sleep here because he was so hard at work he wanted to maximize productivity by not having to have any transit time, or just because he didn't feel like walking? Those with different impressions on him would give different answers.

Other subordinates of his would come and go from here to speak with him. Alfred and Solnit both. Arrive would enter to complain and get in dispute after dispute. A man named Hilbert used to work for Virtos Dextrum, actually. He later ascended into a notable position within the Guard. Just an example of the rich background lore that permeates through this world. Joliene had something of the reverse trajectory, as a guard ultimately becoming affiliated somewhat with Dextrum. This is a setting with significance and history,

The room looks 'lived-in', in other words. A cup of coffee, quite cold by now, is on the desk. File cabinets stuffed to the brim with information. Information on many things. Things such as the Antarctica Project. Personal affects. What personal possessions would Virtos Dextrum have? This is something that merits consideration. Or, would. It can easily be observed in this room. You just have to look. All that is needed is to observe. Someone needs to see. To make it real.
Eulogia and I enter the back room. The one with the trippy cosmic visuals, and with a point of light in the center, and the chrysalis containing The Adversary adjacent to that point.

No time at all.

"I'm sorry. ...Please live a long and happy life." I push Eulogia into the central point before she can react. She disappears. She is no longer here. She is no longer anywhere in this world.

It's done.

I collapse. Bruna Unno collapses to the ground.

For the one initiating the interaction, their physical strength is tested, whereas for the one put on the defense, it can be either physical strength or dexterity. “Mhm.” He uses the computer for a bit longer.

((End chapter))
Is there still a mammoth.
"Oh, okay."
Surprisingly, yes.

Zita steps back.
“You’re all… even you, Joliene? You’re buying this… nonsense?”

“Zita, please.” Virtos begs. “I understand your grief. I do, really. But it isn’t your fault, and it doesn’t have to define you or our world.”
"I'm not. I was speaking hypothetically. The only thing you have to worry about is everybody being too caught up in their own mistaken assumptions to listen to reason."

“Well… okay, I’m… Dextrum… you traitor…!”

“I am no traitor.” Virtos Dextrum shakes his head. “You are closer to that, but I don’t wish to accuse you of any ill intent. Again: nothing that has happened is your fault.” Virtos lies. Everything’s her fucking fault, obviously.

“Shut up! Obviously things that *didn’t happen* are not my fault! Aodh never died! And Bruce is alive, he was just here a moment ago!” She gestures in the direction the wall of force used to exist.

“No. He wasn’t. You’re mistaken.” Virtos shakes his head.

“Bruce was dead for a time, so… at the very least, that end of the claims is less deluded. But he returned! The magic worked! I atoned!!!” She screams.

“There is no scientific backing to the idea that anything about your emotional state or motives could have caused a miscarriage. Why are you being so irrational about this? Despite the front you present, you’re an exceptionally intelligent woman, Zita. Think this through further, and you’ll understand it’s your best option.” Virtos calmly explains.

Zita glares daggers at him. “…This is Earth’s fault, isn’t it? That’s what corrupted you. It corrupted all of my children one by one. Made my sons forget who they were, my daughters forget who they should be. Your idiotic pet project.”

Dextrum sighs.

Zita breathes heavily. She’s taken a lot of hits at this point, even if she’s good at hiding it. She uses her turn to cast something which dissolves the mammoth. 

With the area cleared, Wyrd uses his turn to dash towards Voreverl.

It’s @Natyobb .

Voreverl switches gears as she realizes what just happened, shaking her head to snap herself out of her distracted state. She still silently curses that she didn't get to use her action this turn to use Speak with Animals on the mammoth, though.

Voreverl uses her movement to get up from the prone state, and checks how far away she and Zita are from The Adversary now.
They're not very close anymore. The Adversary is probably going to head this way, but she's no longer in the vicinity the way she was moments ago.
Unable to use a sneak attack, Voreverl decides the best course of action is to make use of her warlock training. She casts four beams of eldritch blast at Zita.
((Each beam gets a different attack roll so 13, 27, 26, 20 with 3, 1, 8, 2 being the respective damage rolls))

The first misses, but as she draws closer, Voreverl is able to hit Zita consistently with the remaining three.

Zita topples over onto the ground, her momentum carrying her tumbling forward to be crumpled in a heap right in front of Voreverl.

Joliene and Zita are disabled. The forces of the monarchy are outnumbered and uncertain. Combat proper ends, for the moment.
An uneasy feeling sets in.
She attempts to crawl back into her wheelchair, initiative being over.
This will take some time.

Voreverl stares down in disgust. The villain kills the hero. Voreverl grabs her shortsword with both hands. The villain kills the villain. Voreverl steadies her grip. The villain disposes of the heap of trash. Voreverl positions her sword over Zita's neck. Voreverl Leocot. Voreverl Leocot. Voreverl Leocot.

I kill her. I'm sorry I took so long, dad.

"Wait, no--!" Virtos extends a hand, but he's nowhere close. He can't stop this. No one can.

Zita freezes, and then shoves Voreverl back. She rips the sword out of herself, tossing it. She screams in agony. Blood pours chaotically through the midsection of her wyrd-shaped bindings like water through a breached dam.
She stares at Voreverl. She stops screaming. A faint smile comes to her face. "...It really should've been Lyra."
Joliene continues for her wheelchair.
Joliene reaches her wheelchair.
Zita's bleeding slows. Her eyes grow clouded. Her knees buckle and lose their strength.

...She takes another step forward.

Zita stares, confused, at her own movement. Perhaps her spirit is unwilling to die quite yet.

Her bindings shift. They tighten. A thread maneuvers itself past her arms and around her neck.

Zita gasps for air. Zita can't breathe.
`Snap.`

Zita's head topples over. It seems whatever she used to keep her hair tied up came off, from the chaos of battle or something. Her face is no longer visible. Wyrd takes a step forward.

"...Voreverl. You should probably leave." Virtos Dextrum speaks in a voice entirely unfamiliar to anyone present. He's normally too stupid to feel fear.
This is good. Joliene had a feeling things were going to work themselves out. Yes.

"I was just waiting for the show to end." Voreverl gives a lazed wave to everyone present. "Have fun working out politics or whatever. Not my problem anymore." She makes a break for whatever looks like the exit.

Wyrd swings his arm at Voreverl. He misses. He goes further. Zita's arm dislocates. Wyrd successfully grabs Voreverl. Wyrd throws Voreverl onto the ground face first. Voreverl breaks her nose.

The Adversary arrives. "Unbelievable. Why would this happen?"

"That outfit. It..." Virtos starts saying something.

"I don't actually care. It's a problem to be dealt with. Zita can't be alive in any sense of the word." The Adversary sighs.

The building shakes.
Voreverl rolls over and feels her nose. "Ow... Whatever, if Zita's dead, I did what I needed to. I can die here for all I care."
"I think... it was a mistake. To underestimate the Crown."

The Crown. That's one way to put it. It lives on. It used Zita as long as it could. And it still does, through the fragment of it she wove into her alternate persona, mimicking her dead husband in a way that makes no sense at all and is in fact entirely unrelated to the way she actually mimicked her husband by performing his administrative duties. It had an ideological link, though. Zita was loyal to the very end, but it's unclear what the hell it is she was loyal *to*.

Maybe there's something poetic, then, about this shambling, unstoppable lifeless body. Is that why magic works the way it does? For whatever facilitates the best descriptive metaphor?

Wyrd uses his weapon and cuts clean through a rebel who tries to approach him. A royal guard near that rebel meets the same fate. The threads continue to writhe and slither and break various parts of Zita's body.

"Seriously, though. Where the hell *did* Rikarasu go?" The Adversary mutters. If anyone is still looking at her, they'd see her hands start to glow black as she runs to Wyrd.

((End chapter.))

Intuition awakens lying on the ground, face up.

(( @[                              ] ))
The building shakes. He’s not in quite the same place he lost consciousness, he can tell that much without getting up.
Am I able to steady myself and get up?
((roll constitution))

Barely, but you feel like you’re about to topple over. There’s a few people who are unconscious-at-best in the vicinity. One is recognizable as Skelt Ageny, who is lying face down with his back covered in blood.
"Is he alive....?"
No one answers this.
I check his pulse.
((roll medicine (or just a fucking flat d20 if you can’t be bothered to check that)))

…You’re not sure. It’s hard to tell. Hard to focus on such a minute detail.

Intuition feels a gun pressed to the back of his head.

“…Hello, Intuition.” Katrielle’s voice. “I’ll save you time. He’s dead.”
"I... I suppose this it it."
"I couldn't save you. I couldn't save antarctica. I couldn't save anyone."
"Do what you will."
“Save me? What the hell are you talking about?” She pulls the gun away.
"I..I wanted to get rid of the patriarchy that restrained them. Catarina.... Zita...you... all of them are victims of it."
“I—I’m not a victim! I’m…” She grabs you by the collar, forcing you to face her.
"I....there is no way that you... you got the inheritance money when dad died! ...I can believed that maybe he triod but... did you ever get it?"
"I *didn't*." She lets go of you, causing you to fall over onto your ass. "You got *everything*. Don't play dumb. You've lived in your own *micronation* these past few years."
((really important to remember and bother with this dumb joke gimmick once every five scenes shes in))
((It's thematically meaningful that she's only doing it now. Trust.))
".......I wasted it.....I didn't know my own strength... I didn't realize! But I realized now, didn't I?"
"There's... there's nothing stopping me from giving it all back."
I recount the loan sharks. ....

"I don't want your *charity*." She drops the gun and reaches into her pocket, pulling out a small magical glow, almost akin to a flame. You've probably seen Skelt with this kind of thing before. "This is what I was after." It shifts to a shape more akin to a 'Camera', like from Earth.
"What is it.....?"

"I don't quite know, but this is Catarina's whole shtick. Recording and replaying events for propaganda purposes. Remember that whole gameshow? It seems she wanted to do the same for her amazing revolution. But now I have it. I can do whatever I want to the footage, splice it to remove my untimely defeat. I'll be a *hero*, Intuition. I'll suck up to these idiot idealists and take what's mine. Information is power! That's what I've learned in all my years."
"...I win."
"There has to be a better option than.....this, mom. You've won, but not with any honest work or the use of truthful information....you've rewritten history sure.... but.... you've...."
I reflect on everything that has happened. "You've....rewritten history."
"This is your only chance. There was an opportunity. You've found that opportunity- and you strike. You've found it."
"I could have never done that....I lost that entire mansion in Japan. I...."
"You've succeeded." I weakly smile. "I'm proud of you."

"Stop--stop rambling! I *won*! I'm the sole heir to Brian Groverfield's possessions now! Me! Your land, your forces, the air you're breathing right fucking now! It's mine! I'll take your mafia connections, too! This whole display will put me in good graces with both the new world order and its underbelly, that Boss guy! How do you like that, huh?!"
"That's fine."
"But... how will you use it? Surely something you've just recieved won't just come to you immediately."
"N--None of your damn business. And no, it'll take a bit of time, but. It's a certainty! I've already made the prearrangements."
"I don't have anything else to say, then."

Her expression shatters.

"What the hell does that mean?!"
"It was with nepotism I got everything I had.... it would only make sense for someone like me to lose it."
"You... that's... you can't just be *OKAY* with this! You owe me! You've been my enemy your whole life! Get mad! Tell me off for how much I've failed you! Cry in despair as I ruin your life!"
"Why can't you just be normal?!"
"Maybe I would be mad. Maybe I would have tried to stop you. But.... but. This is what you wanted! You got what you wanted after all these years! You're happy! I'm happy for you!"
"Shut up! You don't care how I feel! I--!" She takes a step back. She picks up her gun again.
"What have I accomplished in these past few years?"

"No! No! No! The simulation.... the simulation... it's fucking with me again! That's all it does! The fucking adversary! They wanted to come here and laugh at me that nothing will change! That I can't change life one bit!"
"You HAVE to use it! You NEED to use this!"

"I'm your adversary, yes. And I'm-- I don't understand. Do you not understand what's going on at all?? I killed your friend here! I stole from him! I could kill you right now!" She cocks and loads the gun.
"Him?!!! Him?!!! That enabler? He constantly spat nonsense about "protecting women". "protecting" Catarina Praxis. And look where I am now. I'm dead. I didn't do shit."

"You aren't dead! Stop saying nonsense! But you could be! I..."
Katrielle Groverfield starts crying.
"I *hate* you... and that's why I did all this..."
"I..... I.... I..... I....." My face gets red. "You have this power! YOU HAVE THIS ALL! Use it or I'll snatch it from you."
"What are you talking about?! I'm *going* to use it! I... just you wait!" She takes a step back.
*What? What? What? What? Do I do?*
I try to step closer. "That magic you have is mine! I knew it. I knew you were a coward."
"You've explained all your motives to me. And now.... I have all the evidence for you to indict of you numerous crimes, really."
"No one will believe you. You're a lunatic. Boy who cried wolf. You've dug your own grave. Unless you want to man up and try to kill me before I manage this coup? I doubt it. You wouldn't."
"Intuition is when you stop thinking. and you start doing. You yourself should have thought about this before you babbled on about all this." I pull my gun.

Intuition doesn't have a gun.

"I took that. ...You were out of bullets anyway, though." She reaches into her other pocket and tosses it to you. "Worthless."
"And that was your fatal mistake. You know that a blank can still kill someone, right? Heated gasses in the barrel can be shot with enough force to damage something."

"You don't *have* any blanks. Incompetent. I really did fail to raise you, huh? I..." She trails off. Katrielle lifts a hand to her face. She realizes only now that she's crying. Her eyes widen in fear.

"Fuck." Katrielle runs.
I let her run off, and I unload the gun.
The gun is already unloaded. Seriously, what is your goal here.

Or like. There's nothing in the gun. There aren't bullets in the gun. There aren't blanks in the gun. The place where ammunition is stored in a gun does not have anything in it for this gun. Because you don't have any.
"There was a difference between no ammo and blanks?"
Yes. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blank_(cartridge)

The building shakes again, much stronger this time. Things begin to collapse.
